{"title": "Hiding the Handicap", "content": "Having a disability can change the way some people view you as a person. But what if you don't want people to change their image of you?\n\nWell, you could try to hide your handicap.\n\nHiding the Handicap is when a character with a disability or other type of affliction chooses to hide that fact. Reasons for doing this can vary: maybe the character in question believes they can't afford to be seen as \"weak\", maybe they're afraid of being mocked or pitied, or perhaps they'd no longer be allowed to do something if certain people found out. Can overlap with Secretly Dying, if the character has a debilitating mortal injury.\n\nSecret Stab Wound is a short-term version. Contrast Obfuscating Disability and I Am Not Left-Handed.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HidingTheHandicap", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/IrisZero", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/LegendOfGalacticHeroes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/TokyoGhoul", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Vagabond", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/FullmetalAlchemist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DrStone", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Gattaca", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheGreatestShowOnEarth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GrudgeMatch", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JustTheWayYouAre", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/KristyMcNichol", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheLongestDay", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThePrestige", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TotalRecall1990", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SunriseAtCampobello", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/WarmSprings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheCityWithoutMemory", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/CodexAlera", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Genome", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/RoseUnderFire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ASongOfIceAndFire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Wicked", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Arrow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Blackadder", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BoardwalkEmpire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Bos